     wickets3 = 21\n|           bowl avg3 = 30.52\n|            fivefor3 = 0\n|             tenfor3 = 0\n|       best bowling3 = 3/7\n|  catches/stumpings3 = 9/\u2013\n|                date = 13 March\n|                year = 2020\n|              source = https://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/player/455524.html ESPNcricinfo\n}}\n'''Matthew Jack Leach''' (born 22 June 1991) is an English [[cricket]]er who plays for [[Somerset County Cricket Club]] and [[England cricket team|England]]. A spin bowler, he bowls [[left-arm orthodox spin]], and bats left-handed. He made his [[First-class cricket|first-class]] debut for [[Cardiff MCC University]] against Somerset in 2012 before making his debut for Somerset in the tour match against the [[South Africa national cricket team|South Africans]] later in the summer.\n\n==Early life and education==\nLeach was born in [[Taunton]], England on 22 June 1991, and attended Trinity School, [[Bishop Fox's School]] and [[Richard Huish College, Taunton|Richard Huish College]] all in Taunton.<ref name=\"Cricinfo profile\">{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/england/content/player/455524.html |title=Jack Leach Profile |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |accessdate=30 April 2013 }}</ref> He used to be employed to park trolleys at a branch of [[Sainsbury's]] supermarket in Taunton.<ref name=\"Maiden Five-wicket haul\">{{cite news |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/county-cricket-2013/content/story/632900.html |last=Dobell |first=George |title=Warwickshire last pair thwart Somerset |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |date=28 April 2013 |accessdate=30 April 2013 }}</ref> At the age of 14, Leach was diagnosed with [[Crohn's disease]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/46046486 |title=Jack Leach on England, DJing at Jos Buttler's wedding, Crohn's & trolleys |work=BBC Sport |accessdate=2 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/story/_/id/28192460/jack-leach-hospitalised-bout-gastroenteritis |title=Jack Leach hospitalised by bout of gastroenteritis |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=30 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Cricket career==\nLeach graduated from the [[Somerset County Cricket Club]] academy in the summer of 2010,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.somersetcountycc.co.uk/player/jack-leach/ |title=Jack Leach \u2013 Squad |publisher=Somerset County Cricket Club |accessdate=30 April 2013 }}</ref> prior to signing a professional contract with Somerset. Leach represented [[Dorset County Cricket Club]] in the 2010 [[Minor Counties Cricket Championship]], and bowled his side to victory in the final against [[Lincolnshire County Cricket Club|Lincolnshire]] taking 6/21 in their second innings.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/266/266298.html |title=Dorset v Lincolnshire in 2010 |publisher=CricketArchive |accessdate=30 April 2013 }}</ref> Leach completed his degree at the [[University of Wales Institute, Cardiff]] in sports coaching.<ref name=\"MCC University profile\"/> Whilst attending university Leach represented [[Cardiff MCC University|Cardiff MCCU]] in 2011 and 2012 making his first-class debut against his county side Somerset in March 2012, bowling 41 overs but failing to take a wicket as Somerset amassed 642/3[[Declaration and forfeiture|d]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/542465.html |title=Somerset v Cardiff MCCU at Taunton, 31 March \u2013 2 April, 2012 |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |accessdate=30 April 2013 }}</ref>\n\nLeach made his Somerset debut in a two-day match against the [[South African cricket team in England in 2012|touring]] [[South Africa national cricket team|South Africans]] in July 2012, claiming the prized wicket of [[Hashim Amla]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/england-v-south-africa-2012/content/story/571791.html |title=Duminy finds valuable form ahead of Tests |last=Moonda |first=Firdose |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |date=10 July 2012 |accessdate=30 April 2013 }}</ref> He made his first-class debut for Somerset in the [[2012 County Championship]] match against [[Lancashire County Cricket Club|Lancashire]] in August 2012,<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.thisisbristol.co.uk/Spinner-Leach-lined-Somerset-debut-Liverpool/story-16623597-detail/story.html |title=Spinner Leach is lined up for Somerset debut in Liverpool |publisher=The Bristol Post |date=1 August 2012 |accessdate=30 April 2013 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130505155456/http://www.thisisbristol.co.uk/Spinner-Leach-lined-Somerset-debut-Liverpool/story-16623597-detail/story.html |archive-date=5 May 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> the rain affected match finished as a draw with Leach claiming [[Kyle Hogg]] as his maiden first-class wicket.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/county-cricket-2012/content/story/575419.html |title=Prince turns match on its head |last=Hodgson |first=Myles |publisher=ESPNcricinfo |date=3 August 2012 |accessdate=30 April 2013 }}</ref> Further opportunities in the first team were limited for the rest of the 2012 season with the signing of Pakistani spinner [[Abdur Rehman (cricketer, born 1980)|Abdur Rehman]], and Leach only featured in one further County Championship match and three matches in the [[2012 Clydesdale Bank 40]], but ended the season ninth in the national first-class averages with 12 wickets at 18.83 runs apiece.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.somersetcountycc.co.uk/2012/09/jacks-off-to-play-grade-cricket-in-brisbane/ |title=Jack's off to play Grade Cricket in Brisbane |publisher=Somerset County Cricket Club |date=25 September 2012 |accessdate=30 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920235713/http://www.somersetcountycc.co.uk/2012/09/jacks-off-to-play-grade-cricket-in-brisbane/ |archive-date=20 September 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Leach spent the 2012\u201313 winter playing [[grade cricket]] for [[Valley District Cricket Club]] in [[Brisbane]], Australia, helping his side to win the T20 competition.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.somersetcountycc.co.uk/2013/03/jack-leach-aiming-for-championship-opener-against-durham/ |title=Jack Leach aiming for Championship opener against Durham |publisher=Somerset County Cricket Club |date=24 March 2013 |accessdate=30 April 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130526212128/http://www.somersetcountycc.co.uk/2013/03/jack-leach-aiming-for-championship-opener-against-durham/ |archive-date=26 May 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\nLeach returned to Somerset for pre-season on a summer contract and played his first [[2013 County Championship|Championship]] game of the season against [[Warwickshire County Cricket Club|Warwickshire]] due to an injury to first choice spinner [[George Dockrell]]; he took his maiden five-wicket haul in the second innings, with 24 of his 44 overs being maidens.<ref name=\"Maiden Five-wicket haul\"/><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/cricket/22339873 |title=Jack Leach: Somerset spinner frustrated by Bears draw |publisher=BBC Sport |date=30 April 2013 |accessdate=30 April 2013 }}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nOn 14 February 2018, while playing for the [[England Lions (cricket team)|England Lions]] against [[West Indies A]], Leach achieved match figures of 8-110; in doing so, he beat the previous best figures by an England Lions spinner ([[Graeme Swann]]'s 8-156).<ref>{{cite web|title=Jack Leach claims best figures by England Lions spinner during defeat to West Indies A|url=http://www.skysports.com/cricket/news/12173/11250662/jack-leach-claims-best-figures-by-england-lions-spinner-during-defeat-to-west-indies-a|website=Sky Sports|accessdate=14 February 2018|date=14 February 2018}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 March 2018, he was called up to England's [[Test cricket|Test]] squad for the [[English cricket team in New Zealand in 2017\u201318|tour of New Zealand]] as an injury replacement for [[Mason Crane]].<ref>https://www.telegraph.co.uk/cricket/2018/03/16/england-call-jack-leach-replace-injured-mason-crane/</ref> He made his debut in the second Test in [[Christchurch]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/engine/match/1115781.html|title=2nd Test, England tour of Australia and New Zealand at Christchurch, Mar 30 - Apr 3 2018|work=ESPN Cricinfo|accessdate=30 March 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn an unusual circumstance, with 1 over left to play during [[English cricket team in Sri Lanka in 2018\u201319|a Test match against Sri Lanka]] on 15 November 2018, Leach opened England's innings as a [[nightwatchman (cricket)|nightwatchman]], surviving till stumps. He was dismissed for 1 off 11 balls the next morning.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18602/commentary/1140386/sri-lanka-vs-england-2nd-test-eng-in-sl-2018-19|title=2nd Test, England tour of Sri Lanka at Kandy, Nov 14-18 2018|work=ESPN Cricinfo|accessdate=16 November 2018}}</ref> In July 2019, in the one-off Test [[Irish cricket team in England in 2019|against Ireland]], Leach was once again the nightwatchman for England, batting for a single over at the close of day one.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/cricket/49114455 |title=England v Ireland: Jack Leach makes 92 before hosts collapse in Lord's Test |work=BBC Sport |accessdate=26 July 2019}}</ref> England won the Test by 143 runs, with Leach scoring 92 runs, which earned him the man of the match award.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.espncricinfo.com/series/18774/report/1152839/day/3/england-vs-ireland-only-test-ireland-tour-of-england-2019 |title=Chris Woakes and Stuart Broad wreck Ireland dream in a session |work=ESPN Cricinfo |accessdate=26 July 2019}}</ref>\n\nHe was then recalled for the second Ashes test at [[Lord's|Lords]], on 14 August 2019, where he scored 6 not out in the first innings and took 1-19 and 3-37 in Australia's first and second innings respectively. England drew the match.\n\nLeach scored 1 run in a partnership of 76 with [[Ben Stokes]], to help [[England National Cricket Team|England]] win the third Ashes test at [[Headingley Stadium|Headingley]], by 1 wicket.\n\nLeach gained a cult following over the summer of 2019, with his glasses being a contributing factor. He regularly cleans them through his innings, and has received free Specsavers glasses for life following his heroics supporting Ben Stokes in the dramatic Headingley test.<ref>{{cite web |title=Specsavers to offer England's Jack Leach 'free glasses for life' |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/cricket/specsavers-to-offer-englands-jack-leach-free-glasses-for-life-after-ben-stokes-tweet-a4221241.html |website=Evening Standard |language=en |date=25 August 2019}}</ref> This cult reputation was enhanced by his behaviour off the pitch, such as leading some of the England team out to recreate his famous run at Headingley after the match.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dhingra |first1=Himanshu |title=Watch: Jack Leach recreates that single in 76 run partnership with Ben Stokes |url=https://www.livemint.com/sports/cricket-news/watch-jack-leach-recreates-that-single-in-76-run-partnership-with-ben-stokes-1566920791740.html |website=Mint |language=en |date=27 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of people diagnosed with Crohn's disease]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{cricinfo|id=455524}}\n\n{{Somerset County Cricket Club squad}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Leach, Jack}}\n[[Category:1991 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Taunton]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Cardiff Metropolitan University]]\n[[Category:English cricketers]]\n[[Category:England Test cricketers]]\n[[Category:Dorset cricketers]]\n[[Category:Cardiff MCCU cricketers]]\n[[Category:Somerset cricketers]]\n[[Category:Marylebone Cricket Club cricketers]]\n[[Category:People with Crohn's disease]]\n", "name_user": "77.102.168.105", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jack_Leach"}
{"title_page": "Halal (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2016 film by Shivaji Lotan Patil}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Halal\n| image          = Halal film poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Shivaji Lotan Patil]]\n| producer       = Amol Kagne<br/>Laxman Kagne\n| writer         = Rajan Khan\n| screenplay     = Nishant Dhapse\n| based on       = {{Based on|Halal|Rajan Khan}}\n| starring       = [[Chinmay Mandlekar]]<br /> [[Priyadarshan Jadhav]] <br /> [[Pritam Kagne]] <br /> [[Vijay Chavan]] <br /> Amol Kagne\n| music          = Vijay Gatlewar\n| cinematography = Ramani Ranjan Das\n| editing        = Nilesh Gavand\n| studio = Amol Kagne Films\n| released       = {{film date|df=y|2016|01||PIFF|ref1=<ref name=\"piff:l1\"/>|2017|10|6}} \n|runtime         = 148 Minutes\n|country         = India\n|language        = Marathi\n|budget          = \n|gross           = \n}}\n'''''Halal''''' (Marathi: \u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932) is 2017 [[Marathi language]] [[Muslim social|social]] [[Drama (film and television)|drama]] film, directed by national award-winning director [[Shivaji Lotan Patil]] and produced by Amol Kagne, Laxman Kagne under the banner of Amol Kagne Productions. It is their first film, and it deals with the theme of loyalty, love and the institution of marriage that is deemed to be pious by the society. Portraying the family system of Indian Muslims, the film depicts human emotions, and the trials and the tribulations that women in our society go through. The film features [[Chinmay Mandlekar]], [[Priyadarshan Jadhav]], [[Pritam Kagne]] and [[Vijay Chavan]] in pivotal roles.\n\n''Halal'' was premiered at the [[Pune International Film Festival]] 2016.<ref name=\"piff:l1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.piffindia.com/awards.html |title=PUNE INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL (PIFF) |website=www.piffindia.com |access-date=2016-03-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160111222135/http://www.piffindia.com/awards.html |archive-date=11 January 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> It was also screened at the 2016 Aurangabad International Film Festival.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.loksatta.com/manoranjan-news/halal-movie-selected-for-aurangabad-international-film-festival-1195994/ |title=\u0914\u0930\u0902\u0917\u093e\u092c\u093e\u0926 \u0906\u0902\u0924\u0930\u0930\u093e\u0937\u094d\u091f\u094d\u0930\u0940\u092f \u091a\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0930\u092a\u091f \u092e\u0939\u094b\u0924\u094d\u0938\u0935\u093e\u0924 \u2018\u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932\u2019 |website=Loksatta |language=en-US |access-date=2016-03-17}}</ref> The film was screened at the [[Cannes Film Festival]] and at Goa Marathi Film Festival 2016.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web |url=http://marathicineyug.com/news/latest-news/1237-halal-receives-overwhelming-response-at-goa-film-festival |title=\u2018Halal\u2019 receives overwhelming response at Goa Film Festival - Marathi Cineyug |last=Kulye |first=Ajay |website=marathicineyug.com |access-date=2016-06-09}}</ref> \n\nThe film was theatrically released on 6 October 2017.\n\n==Synopsis==\nHalim is divorced by her husband, but  he comes back deciding to re-marry her. As per religion Halim has to undergo  [[Nikah halala|halala]], that she has to marry another man, consummate relationship, divorce him and then marry her first husband. A Maulana offers to do that. Maulana showers her with love and care and she gets confused between staying and leaving the current marriage. \n\n==Cast==\n* [[Chinmay Mandlekar]]\n* [[Priyadarshan Jadhav]] \n* [[Pritam Kagne]]\n* [[Vijay Chavan]]\n* Amol Kagne\n* Chhaya Kadam\n* Vimal Mhatre\n\n==Production==\nAmol Kagne and Laxman Kagne produced this movie. Story and dialogues written by Nishant Dhapse, DOP is Ramani Ranjandas, editing by Nilesh Gavand. Music given by Vijay Gatlewar and songs sung by Adarsh Shinde and Vijay Gatlewar.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url=http://huntnews.in/p/detail/6951b51ded6945c898dc397e8bd6a7ff?xlang=en&uc_param_str=dnfrpfbivesscpgimibtbmntnisieijblauputoggdnw&pos=1453299431924&channel=entertainment&chncat=english |title=First Screening of 'Halal' in PIFF |website=huntnews.in |access-date=2016-03-17}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe official trailer of the film was unveiled by Rajshri Marathi on 14 September 2017.<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=m-gHmj9e6Qs|title=Halal (\u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932) - Official Trailer - Marathi Movie 2017 - Chinmay Mandlekar, Priyadarshan Jadhav|work=Rajshri Marathi|publisher=YouTube|date=14 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe film was theatrically released on 6 October 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://punemirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi-reviews/film-halal/articleshow/60975075.cms|title=FILM: HALAL|website=Pune Mirror}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi/movie-reviews/halal/movie-review/60973107.cms|title=Halal Movie Review {3.5/5}: Critic Review of Halal by Times of India|via=timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref>\n\n===Reception===\n''Halal'' was screened at the [[Pune International Film Festival]], the Yashvantrao Chavan International Film Festival and the Aurangabad International Film Festival.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mymarathi.net/filmy-mania/halal-2/ |title=\u0914\u0930\u0902\u0917\u093e\u092c\u093e\u0926 \u0906\u0902\u0924\u0930\u0930\u093e\u0937\u094d\u091f\u094d\u0930\u0940\u092f \u091a\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0930\u092a\u091f \u092e\u0939\u094b\u0924\u094d\u0938\u0935\u093e\u0924 \u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932 - My Marathi |website=mymarathi.net |access-date=2016-10-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mumbainewsnetwork.blogspot.in/2016/01/blog-post_81.html |title=\u0914\u0930\u0902\u0917\u093e\u092c\u093e\u0926 \u0906\u0902\u0924\u0930\u0930\u093e\u0937\u094d\u091f\u094d\u0930\u0940\u092f \u091a\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0930\u092a\u091f \u092e\u0939\u094b\u0924\u094d\u0938\u0935\u093e\u0924 \u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932 |website=mumbainewsnetwork.blogspot.in |access-date=2016-10-12}}</ref> The film has received highly positive reviews from audience, critics & media.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.filmibeat.com/marathi-movies/news/halal-nominated-for-piff-2016-212296.html |title='Halal' Nominated for PIFF 2016! |website=www.filmibeat.com |access-date=2016-03-17}}</ref> Screenplay writer Nishant Dhapse won the \"Best Marathi Screenplay Award\" at [[Pune International Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.piffindia.com/awards.html |title=PUNE INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL (PIFF) |website=www.piffindia.com |access-date=2016-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160111222135/http://www.piffindia.com/awards.html |archive-date=11 January 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> ''Halal'' was also screened at the [[Cannes Film Festival]], scheduled between 11 and 22 May 2016.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.zeetalkies.com/celebs-speak/three-marathi-films-to-be-screened-at-cannes-international-film-fest.html |title=Three Marathi Films To Be Screened At Cannes International Film Fest |website=ZEE Talkies |access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref> Halal was also screened at the Goa Film Festival, receiving overwhelming response.There were about 20 films screened during this film festival, including one Konkani film.<ref name=\":5\" /> Halal was screened at the Godrej International Film Festival 2016 on 12 August 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://allevents.in/mumbai/halal-marathi-cinema-now-opening-screening/266887820351609 |title=Halal : Marathi Cinema Now Opening Screening |website=allevents.in |access-date=2016-08-15}}</ref> ''Halal'' was screened at the 47th [[International Film Festival of India]] was held during 20 to 28 November 2016 at Goa.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://orientpublication.wordpress.com/2016/10/18/%e0%a4%87%e0%a4%ab%e0%a5%8d%e0%a4%ab%e0%a5%80%e0%a4%a4-%e0%a4%9d%e0%a4%b3%e0%a4%95%e0%a4%a3%e0%a4%be%e0%a4%b0-%e0%a4%b9%e0%a4%b2%e0%a4%be%e0%a4%b2/ |title=\u2018\u0907\u092b\u094d\u092b\u0940\u2019\u0924 \u091d\u0933\u0915\u0923\u093e\u0930 \u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932 |date=2016-10-18 |website=ORIENT PUBLICATION |access-date=2016-10-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.rangmaitra.com/halal-iffi/ |title=\u2018\u0907\u092b\u094d\u092b\u0940\u2019\u0924 \u091d\u0933\u0915\u0923\u093e\u0930 \u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932 |newspaper=Rangmaitra |access-date=2016-10-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.loksatta.com/manoranjan-news/halal-movie-in-iffi-1319992/ |title=\u2018\u0907\u092b\u094d\u092b\u0940\u2019\u0924 \u091d\u0933\u0915\u0923\u093e\u0930 \u2018\u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932\u2019 |date=2016-10-17 |newspaper=Loksatta |language=mr-IN |access-date=2016-10-18}}</ref> ''Halal'' was screened at the Delhi International Film Festival 2016 held between 3 and 9 December at Central Park and NDMC Convention Centre, Connaught Place [[New Delhi]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.delhiinternationalfilmfestival.com/indian-showcase/ |title=INDIAN SHOWCASE |date=2015-05-06 |newspaper=Diff |language=en-US |access-date=2016-11-11}}</ref> The film is also scheduled to screen at Asian Film Festival.\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Halal\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = Vijay Gatlewar\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|9|13}}\n| recorded   = 2017\n| venue      =\n| studio     = \n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 8:35\n| language   = [[Marathi language|Marathi]]\n| label      = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = \n| prev_year  = \n| next_title = \n| next_year  =\n| misc = {{External media\n| audio1 = {{YouTube|kAz0pMseNm8|Audio Jukebox}}}}\n}}\n\nThe songs for the film are composed by  Vijay Gatlewar and lyrics by Subodh Pawar and Sayed Akhtar.\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline    = Track list\n| total_length= 8:35\n| extra_column=Singer(s)\n| title1  = Maula Maula Mera Maula\n| length1 = 5:19\n| lyrics1 = Subodh Pawar and Sayed Akhtar\n| extra1  = Adarsha Shinde, Vijay Gatlewar\n| title2  = Saiya Mera Saiya\n| length2 = 3:16\n| lyrics2 = Subodh Pawar\n| extra2  = Vijay Gatlewar\n}}\n\n== Accolades ==\n''Halal'' film garnered many awards and nominations in several categories with praise for Shivaji Lotan-Patil's direction, cinematography, production design, costumes, and cast's performances. At the [[Maharashtra State Film Awards]] 2016, the film won 6 awards.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web |url=http://marathicineyug.com/news/latest-news/833-53rd-maharashtra-state-film-awards-2016-full-nominations-list |title=53rd Maharashtra State Film Awards 2016: Full Nominations List - Marathi Cineyug |last=Kulye |first=Ajay |website=marathicineyug.com |access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref> It was also nominated for ''Sanskruti Kaladarpan Awards 2016.''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Ceremony\n!Category\n!Nominee\n!Result\n!Ref.\n|-\n|53rd [[Maharashtra State Film Awards]]\n|Best Film in social issue category\n|''Halal''\n|Won\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|\n|Best debut Film Production\n|Amol Kagne Films\n|Won\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|\n|Best Social Issue Director\n|Shivaji Lotan-Patil\n|Won\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|\n|Best Writer\n|Rajan Khan\n|Won\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|\n|Best Background Music\n|Honey Satamkar\n|Won\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|\n|Best Lyricist\n|Sayeed Akhtar\n|Won\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|Sanskruti Kala Darpan Awards 2016\n|Best Feature Film\n|''Halal''\n|Nominated\n|<ref name=\":3\">{{Cite web |url=http://starmarathi.in/nominations-for-sanskruti-kala-darpan-2016-announced/ |title=Nominations for Sanskruti Kala Darpan 2016 Announced |date=2016-04-16 |website=StarMarathi.in |language=en-US |access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref>\n|-\n|\n|Best Debut Actor\n|Pritam Kagne\n|Nominated\n|<ref name=\":3\" />\n|-\n|\n|Best Writer\n|Rajan Khan\n|Nominated\n|<ref name=\":3\" />\n|-\n|4th Indian Cine Film Festival-2016\n|Best Social Film\n|Halal\n|Won\n|<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://miniboxoffice.com/indiancinefilmfestival/ |title=::: Indian Cine Film Festival::: |website=miniboxoffice.com |access-date=2016-10-01}}</ref>\n|-\n|Sahyadri Cine Awards 2016\n|Best Social Film\n|Halal\n|Nominated\n|\n|-\n|\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|Chinmay Mandalekar\n|Nominated\n|\n|-\n|\n|Best Actress\n|Pritam Kagne\n|Nominated\n|\n|-\n|\n|Best Story\n|Rajan Khan\n|Nominated\n|\n|-\n|\n|Best Lyricist\n|Subodh Powar, Sayyad Akhtar\n|Nominated\n|\n|-\n|Zee Gaurav 2017\n|Best Supporting Actor\n|Priyadarshan Jadhav\n|Won\n|\n|-\n|\n|Best Story\n|Rajan Khan\n|Won\n|\n|}\n\n==See also==\n[[List of Marathi films]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|5511856|Halal}}\n\n[[Category:2016 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Marathi-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian drama films]]\n[[Category:Indian women in film]]\n[[Category:2010s Marathi-language films]]\n[[Category:Films about social issues in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2016 film by Shivaji Lotan Patil}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2017}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2017}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Halal\n| image          = Halal film poster.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Shivaji Lotan Patil]]\n| producer       = Amol Kagne<br/>Laxman Kagne\n| writer         = Rajan Khan\n| screenplay     = Nishant Dhapse\n| based on       = {{Based on|Halal|Rajan Khan}}\n| starring       = [[Chinmay Mandlekar]]<br /> [[Priyadarshan Jadhav]] <br /> [[Pritam Kagne]] <br /> [[Vijay Chavan]] <br /> Amol Kagne\n| music          = Vijay Gatlewar\n| cinematography = Ramani Ranjan Das\n| editing        = Nilesh Gavand\n| studio = Amol Kagne Films\n| released       = {{film date|df=y|2016|01||PIFF|ref1=<ref name=\"piff:l1\"/>|2017|10|6}} \n|runtime         = 148 Minutes\n|country         = India\n|language        = Marathi\n|budget          = \n|gross           = \n}}\n'''''Halal''''' (Marathi: \u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932) is 2017 [[Marathi language]] [[Muslim social|social]] [[Drama (film and television)|drama]] film, directed by national award-winning director [[Shivaji Lotan Patil]] and produced by Amol Kagne, Laxman Kagne under the banner of Amol Kagne Productions. It is their first ever film, and it deals with the theme of loyalty, love and the institution of marriage that is deemed to be pious by the society. Portraying family system of Indian Muslims, the film depicts human emotions, and the trials and the tribulations that women in our society go through. The film features [[Chinmay Mandlekar]], [[Priyadarshan Jadhav]], [[Pritam Kagne]] and [[Vijay Chavan]] in pivotal roles.\n\n''Halal'' was premiered at the [[Pune International Film Festival]] 2016.<ref name=\"piff:l1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.piffindia.com/awards.html |title=PUNE INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL (PIFF) |website=www.piffindia.com |access-date=2016-03-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160111222135/http://www.piffindia.com/awards.html |archive-date=11 January 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> It was also screened at the 2016 Aurangabad International Film Festival.<ref name=\":1\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.loksatta.com/manoranjan-news/halal-movie-selected-for-aurangabad-international-film-festival-1195994/ |title=\u0914\u0930\u0902\u0917\u093e\u092c\u093e\u0926 \u0906\u0902\u0924\u0930\u0930\u093e\u0937\u094d\u091f\u094d\u0930\u0940\u092f \u091a\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0930\u092a\u091f \u092e\u0939\u094b\u0924\u094d\u0938\u0935\u093e\u0924 \u2018\u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932\u2019 |website=Loksatta |language=en-US |access-date=2016-03-17}}</ref> The film was screened at the [[Cannes Film Festival]] and at Goa Marathi Film Festival 2016.<ref name=\":5\">{{Cite web |url=http://marathicineyug.com/news/latest-news/1237-halal-receives-overwhelming-response-at-goa-film-festival |title=\u2018Halal\u2019 receives overwhelming response at Goa Film Festival - Marathi Cineyug |last=Kulye |first=Ajay |website=marathicineyug.com |access-date=2016-06-09}}</ref> \n\nThe film was theatrically released on 6 October 2017.\n\n==Synopsis==\nHalim is divorced by her husband, but  he comes back deciding to re-marry her. As per religion Halim has to undergo  [[Nikah halala|halala]], that she has to marry another man, consummate relationship, divorce him and then marry her first husband. A Maulana offers to do that. Maulana showers her with love and care and she gets confused between staying and leaving the current marriage. \n\n==Cast==\n* [[Chinmay Mandlekar]]\n* [[Priyadarshan Jadhav]] \n* [[Pritam Kagne]]\n* [[Vijay Chavan]]\n* Amol Kagne\n* Chhaya Kadam\n* Vimal Mhatre\n\n==Production==\nAmol Kagne and Laxman Kagne produced this movie. Story and dialogues written by Nishant Dhapse, DOP is Ramani Ranjandas, editing by Nilesh Gavand. Music given by Vijay Gatlewar and songs sung by Adarsh Shinde and Vijay Gatlewar.<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite web |url=http://huntnews.in/p/detail/6951b51ded6945c898dc397e8bd6a7ff?xlang=en&uc_param_str=dnfrpfbivesscpgimibtbmntnisieijblauputoggdnw&pos=1453299431924&channel=entertainment&chncat=english |title=First Screening of 'Halal' in PIFF |website=huntnews.in |access-date=2016-03-17}}</ref>\n\n==Release==\nThe official trailer of the film was unveiled by Rajshri Marathi on 14 September 2017.<ref>{{cite AV media|url=https://youtube.com/watch?v=m-gHmj9e6Qs|title=Halal (\u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932) - Official Trailer - Marathi Movie 2017 - Chinmay Mandlekar, Priyadarshan Jadhav|work=Rajshri Marathi|publisher=YouTube|date=14 September 2017}}</ref>\n\nThe film was theatrically released on 6 October 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://punemirror.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi-reviews/film-halal/articleshow/60975075.cms|title=FILM: HALAL|website=Pune Mirror}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/marathi/movie-reviews/halal/movie-review/60973107.cms|title=Halal Movie Review {3.5/5}: Critic Review of Halal by Times of India|via=timesofindia.indiatimes.com}}</ref>\n\n===Reception===\n''Halal'' was screened at the [[Pune International Film Festival]], the Yashvantrao Chavan International Film Festival and the Aurangabad International Film Festival.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mymarathi.net/filmy-mania/halal-2/ |title=\u0914\u0930\u0902\u0917\u093e\u092c\u093e\u0926 \u0906\u0902\u0924\u0930\u0930\u093e\u0937\u094d\u091f\u094d\u0930\u0940\u092f \u091a\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0930\u092a\u091f \u092e\u0939\u094b\u0924\u094d\u0938\u0935\u093e\u0924 \u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932 - My Marathi |website=mymarathi.net |access-date=2016-10-12}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://mumbainewsnetwork.blogspot.in/2016/01/blog-post_81.html |title=\u0914\u0930\u0902\u0917\u093e\u092c\u093e\u0926 \u0906\u0902\u0924\u0930\u0930\u093e\u0937\u094d\u091f\u094d\u0930\u0940\u092f \u091a\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0930\u092a\u091f \u092e\u0939\u094b\u0924\u094d\u0938\u0935\u093e\u0924 \u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932 |website=mumbainewsnetwork.blogspot.in |access-date=2016-10-12}}</ref> The film has received highly positive reviews from audience, critics & media.<ref name=\":1\" /><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.filmibeat.com/marathi-movies/news/halal-nominated-for-piff-2016-212296.html |title='Halal' Nominated for PIFF 2016! |website=www.filmibeat.com |access-date=2016-03-17}}</ref> Screenplay writer Nishant Dhapse won the \"Best Marathi Screenplay Award\" at [[Pune International Film Festival]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.piffindia.com/awards.html |title=PUNE INTERNATIONAL FILM FESTIVAL (PIFF) |website=www.piffindia.com |access-date=2016-05-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160111222135/http://www.piffindia.com/awards.html |archive-date=11 January 2016 |url-status=dead }}</ref> ''Halal'' was also screened at the [[Cannes Film Festival]], scheduled between 11 and 22 May 2016.<ref name=\":4\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.zeetalkies.com/celebs-speak/three-marathi-films-to-be-screened-at-cannes-international-film-fest.html |title=Three Marathi Films To Be Screened At Cannes International Film Fest |website=ZEE Talkies |access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref> Halal was also screened at the Goa Film Festival, receiving overwhelming response.There were about 20 films screened during this film festival, including one Konkani film.<ref name=\":5\" /> Halal was screened at the Godrej International Film Festival 2016 on 12 August 2016.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://allevents.in/mumbai/halal-marathi-cinema-now-opening-screening/266887820351609 |title=Halal : Marathi Cinema Now Opening Screening |website=allevents.in |access-date=2016-08-15}}</ref> ''Halal'' was screened at the 47th [[International Film Festival of India]] was held during 20 to 28 November 2016 at Goa.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://orientpublication.wordpress.com/2016/10/18/%e0%a4%87%e0%a4%ab%e0%a5%8d%e0%a4%ab%e0%a5%80%e0%a4%a4-%e0%a4%9d%e0%a4%b3%e0%a4%95%e0%a4%a3%e0%a4%be%e0%a4%b0-%e0%a4%b9%e0%a4%b2%e0%a4%be%e0%a4%b2/ |title=\u2018\u0907\u092b\u094d\u092b\u0940\u2019\u0924 \u091d\u0933\u0915\u0923\u093e\u0930 \u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932 |date=2016-10-18 |website=ORIENT PUBLICATION |access-date=2016-10-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.rangmaitra.com/halal-iffi/ |title=\u2018\u0907\u092b\u094d\u092b\u0940\u2019\u0924 \u091d\u0933\u0915\u0923\u093e\u0930 \u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932 |newspaper=Rangmaitra |access-date=2016-10-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.loksatta.com/manoranjan-news/halal-movie-in-iffi-1319992/ |title=\u2018\u0907\u092b\u094d\u092b\u0940\u2019\u0924 \u091d\u0933\u0915\u0923\u093e\u0930 \u2018\u0939\u0932\u093e\u0932\u2019 |date=2016-10-17 |newspaper=Loksatta |language=mr-IN |access-date=2016-10-18}}</ref> ''Halal'' was screened at the Delhi International Film Festival 2016 held between 3 and 9 December at Central Park and NDMC Convention Centre, Connaught Place [[New Delhi]].<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.delhiinternationalfilmfestival.com/indian-showcase/ |title=INDIAN SHOWCASE |date=2015-05-06 |newspaper=Diff |language=en-US |access-date=2016-11-11}}</ref> The film is also scheduled to screen at Asian Film Festival.\n\n==Soundtrack==\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Halal\n| type       = Soundtrack\n| artist     = Vijay Gatlewar\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{Start date|df=yes|2017|9|13}}\n| recorded   = 2017\n| venue      =\n| studio     = \n| genre      = [[Film soundtrack|Feature film soundtrack]]\n| length     = 8:35\n| language   = [[Marathi language|Marathi]]\n| label      = [[Zee Music Company]]\n| producer   =\n| prev_title = \n| prev_year  = \n| next_title = \n| next_year  =\n| misc = {{External media\n| audio1 = {{YouTube|kAz0pMseNm8|Audio Jukebox}}}}\n}}\n\nThe songs for the film are composed by  Vijay Gatlewar and lyrics by Subodh Pawar and Sayed Akhtar.\n\n{{Track listing\n| headline    = Track list\n| total_length= 8:35\n| extra_column=Singer(s)\n| title1  = Maula Maula Mera Maula\n| length1 = 5:19\n| lyrics1 = Subodh Pawar and Sayed Akhtar\n| extra1  = Adarsha Shinde, Vijay Gatlewar\n| title2  = Saiya Mera Saiya\n| length2 = 3:16\n| lyrics2 = Subodh Pawar\n| extra2  = Vijay Gatlewar\n}}\n\n== Accolades ==\n''Halal'' film garnered many awards and nominations in several categories with praise for Shivaji Lotan-Patil's direction, cinematography, production design, costumes, and cast's performances. At the [[Maharashtra State Film Awards]] 2016, the film won 6 awards.<ref name=\":2\">{{Cite web |url=http://marathicineyug.com/news/latest-news/833-53rd-maharashtra-state-film-awards-2016-full-nominations-list |title=53rd Maharashtra State Film Awards 2016: Full Nominations List - Marathi Cineyug |last=Kulye |first=Ajay |website=marathicineyug.com |access-date=2016-05-06}}</ref> It was also nominated for ''Sanskruti Kaladarpan Awards 2016.''\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Ceremony\n!Category\n!Nominee\n!Result\n!Ref.\n|-\n|53rd [[Maharashtra State Film Awards]]\n|Best Film in social issue category\n|''Halal''\n|Won\n|<ref name=\":2\" />\n|-\n|\n|Best debut Film Pr