{"title_page": "Miguel Sebasti\u00e1n Garcia", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Pitu\n| fullname = Miguel Sebasti\u00e1n Garcia\n| height = 1.74 m\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1984|1|27}}\n| birth_place = [[Santa Fe, Argentina]]\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub =\n| clubnumber =\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 2004\u20132009\n| years2 = 2006\u20132007\n| years3 = 2007\u20132009\n| years4 = 2009\u20132010\n| years5 = 2010\u20132011\n| years6 = 2011\u20132016\n| years7 = 2016\u20132017\n| years8 = 2017\n| years9 = 2017\u20132019\n| years10 = 2019\u20132020\n| clubs1 = [[Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe]]\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[CD Palestino|Palestino]] (loan)\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Iraklis Thessaloniki F.C.|Iraklis]] (loan)\n| clubs4 = [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]\n| clubs5 = [[Iraklis Thessaloniki F.C.|Iraklis]]\n| clubs6 = [[Atromitos F.C.|Atromitos]]\n| clubs7 = [[Seongnam FC|Seongnam]]\n| clubs8 = [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]\n| clubs9 = [[Volos N.F.C.|Volos]]\n| clubs10 = [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]]\n| caps1 = 61\n| caps2 = 10\n| caps3 = 45\n| caps4 = 10\n| caps5 = 35\n| caps6 = 116\n| caps7 = 33\n| caps8 = 18\n| caps9 = 55\n| caps10 = 7\n| goals1 = 3\n| goals2 = 1\n| goals3 = 3\n| goals4 = 0\n| goals5 = 1\n| goals6 = 2\n| goals7 = 3\n| goals8 = 1\n| goals9 = 14\n| goals10 = 0\n| totalcaps = 390\n| totalgoals = 28\n}}\n\n'''Miguel Sebasti\u00e1n Garcia''' (born 27 January 1984), nicknamed \"'''Pitu'''\", is an Argentine former professional [[association footballer|footballer]] who played as a  [[midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Argentina===\nPitu was born in [[Santa Fe, Argentina|Santa Fe]]. He started his career in [[Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe]], base in his hometown, from which he was loaned firstly to [[CD Palestino|Palestino]] and subsequently to Iraklis. After being released by Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe he played for a brief period for [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]] in the Greek Superleague, before returning on a free transfer to Iraklis during the 2010 winter transfer window.\n\n===Iraklis===\nPitu joined [[Iraklis F.C.|Iraklis]] on loan during the summer of 2007. He made his league debut for his new club in a match against [[Atromitos F.C.|Atromitos]] for the fifth round of the [[2007\u201308 Superleague Greece|2007\u201308 season]], replacing [[Giannis Papadopoulos]] in the 56th minute of the match.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/matchStories/172682.html|script-title=el:\u0391\u03c4\u03c1\u03cc\u03bc\u03b7\u03c4\u03bf\u03c2-\u0397\u03c1\u03b1\u03ba\u03bb\u03ae\u03c2 1-1|date=21 October 2007|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> He continued to appear regularly for the club until the end of the season and he even managed to score his first goal for Iraklis, in a match against [[OFI Crete|OFI]].<ref name=\"OFI\">{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/matchStories/193320.html|script-title=el:\u0397\u03c1\u03b1\u03ba\u03bb\u03ae\u03c2-\u039f\u03a6\u0397 1-0|date=30 March 2008|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> It was a crucial, match deciding, goal, scored in the injury time of the match, disengaging Iraklis from the relegation battle.<ref name=\"OFI\"/> In the end of the season he counted 1 goal out of 20 league appearances.\n\n===Aris===\nOn 31 August 2009, Pitu signed for [[Aris F.C. (Thessaloniki)|Aris]] on a free transfer.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=insports.gr|url=http://www.insports.gr/index.php?s=1&c=1&p=479&cat=7&arthro=19076&nav=%C1%D1%C7%D3:%20-%D0%DF%F4%EF%F5-%20%C3%EA%E1%F1%F3%DF%E1%20%EF%2013%EF%F2|script-title=el:\u0391\u03a1\u0397\u03a3: -\u03a0\u03af\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5- \u0393\u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1 \u03bf 13\u03bf\u03c2|date=31 August 2009|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> He made his debut for Aris in a 1\u20131 away draw against [[Panthrakikos]], as he replaced his teammate [[Darcy Dolce Neto|Neto]] in the 76th minute.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/Soccer/Hellas/Superleague/Panthrakikos_Aris/251612.html|script-title=el:\u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b8\u03c1\u03b1\u03ba\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2-\u0386\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 1-1|date=3 October 2009|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> Pitu scored his only goal for Aris in a cup match against [[Aspropyrgos Enosis|Aspropyrgos]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/Soccer/Hellas/GreekCup/Aspropyrgos_Aris/253802.html|script-title=el:\u0391\u03c3\u03c0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c0\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03bf\u03c2-\u0386\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 3-4|date=28 October 2010|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> He contributed in Aris' campaign as, in a match against [[AEL 1964 FC|AEL]], he hit the corner by which his teammate [[Sebastian Abreu]] scored the equaliser for his team.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/Soccer/Hellas/Superleague/Larisa_Aris/254026.html|script-title=el:\u0391\u0395\u039b - \u0386\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 2-2|date=31 October 2009|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> He managed to appear in total of 10 matches for Aris before being released by the club on 1 February 2010.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/Soccer/Hellas/Superleague/Aris/262350.html|script-title=el:\u03a4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bf \u03a0\u03af\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0393\u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u0386\u03c1\u03b7|date=1 February 2010|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Iraklis===\nOn the very same day of his release Pitu signed a contract with former club [[Iraklis F.C.|Iraklis]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=in.gr|url=http://sports.in.gr/football/superleague/article/?aid=1101381|script-title=el:\u039f \u0397\u03c1\u03b1\u03ba\u03bb\u03ae\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bc\u03c6\u03ce\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b5 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03a0\u03af\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0393\u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03a1\u03b9\u03bc\u03cc\u03bb\u03bd\u03c4\u03b9|date=1 February 2010|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> The debut in this second spell for Iraklis was made in a local derby match against [[PAOK F.C.|PAOK]] that ended 1\u20131.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/Soccer/Hellas/Superleague/Iraklis_PAOK/262926.html|script-title=el:\u0397\u03c1\u03b1\u03ba\u03bb\u03ae\u03c2 - \u03a0\u0391\u039f\u039a 1-1|date=7 February 2010|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> Until the end of the season he featured in a total of ten games for Iraklis.\n\n===Atromitos===\nFollowing the Iraklis's relegation, he joined [[Superleague Greece|Greek First Division]] side [[Atromitos F.C.|Atromitos]] on 29 June 2011, signing a two-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atromitosfc.gr/english/news/details/?id=645|title=Pitu Garcia inks Atromitos FC contract|publisher=[[Atromitos FC]]|date=29 June 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110929001941/http://www.atromitosfc.gr/english/news/details/?id=645|archivedate=29 September 2011}}</ref>\n\n===PAS Giannina===\nOn 5 August 2019, Pitu signed for [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]] on a free transfer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pasgiannina.gr/transfer/welcome-miguel-sebastian-pitu-garcia/|title=WELCOME MIGUEL SEBASTI\u00c1N \u00abPITU\u00bb GARC\u00cdA|date=5 August 2019}}</ref> He appeared in total of 9 matches, 7 in the championship and 2 in the [[Greek Cup]]. After the end of a match against [[Levadiakos F.C.|Levadiakos]], he announced his decision to retire from football.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://super-fm.gr/54908/pitoy-pira-tin-apofasi-na-stamatiso-to-podosfairo-quot/|title=\u03a0\u03af\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5: \u00ab\u03a0\u03ae\u03c1\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc\u03c6\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7 \u03bd\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03ae\u03c3\u03c9 \u03c4\u03bf \u03c0\u03bf\u03b4\u03cc\u03c3\u03c6\u03b1\u03b9\u03c1\u03bf\u00bb|last=|first=|date=20 January 2020|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{BDFA|31298}}\n* {{K League player|20160242}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garcia, Miguel Sebastian}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Santa Fe, Argentina]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Argentine footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Aris Thessaloniki F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Iraklis Thessaloniki F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Club Deportivo Palestino footballers]]\n[[Category:Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe footballers]]\n[[Category:Atromitos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Volos N.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:PAS Giannina F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Seongnam FC players]]\n[[Category:Super League Greece players]]\n[[Category:K League 1 players]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Chile]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Greece]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in South Korea]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate sportspeople in South Korea]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Pitu\n| fullname = Miguel Sebasti\u00e1n Garcia\n| height = 1.74 m\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1984|1|27}}\n| birth_place = [[Santa Fe, Argentina]]\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub =\n| clubnumber =\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 2004\u20132009\n| years2 = 2006\u20132007\n| years3 = 2007\u20132009\n| years4 = 2009\u20132010\n| years5 = 2010\u20132011\n| years6 = 2011\u20132016\n| years7 = 2016\u20132017\n| years8 = 2017\n| years9 = 2017\u20132019\n| years10 = 2019\u20132020\n| clubs1 = [[Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe]]\n| clubs2 = \u2192 [[CD Palestino|Palestino]] (loan)\n| clubs3 = \u2192 [[Iraklis Thessaloniki F.C.|Iraklis]] (loan)\n| clubs4 = [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]\n| clubs5 = [[Iraklis Thessaloniki F.C.|Iraklis]]\n| clubs6 = [[Atromitos F.C.|Atromitos]]\n| clubs7 = [[Seongnam FC|Seongnam]]\n| clubs8 = [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]]\n| clubs9 = [[Volos N.F.C.|Volos]]\n| clubs10 = [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]]\n| caps1 = 61\n| caps2 = 10\n| caps3 = 45\n| caps4 = 10\n| caps5 = 35\n| caps6 = 116\n| caps7 = 33\n| caps8 = 18\n| caps9 = 55\n| caps10 = 7\n| goals1 = 3\n| goals2 = 1\n| goals3 = 3\n| goals4 = 0\n| goals5 = 1\n| goals6 = 2\n| goals7 = 3\n| goals8 = 1\n| goals9 = 14\n| goals10 = 0\n| totalcaps = 390\n| totalgoals = 28\n}}\n\n'''Miguel Sebasti\u00e1n Garcia''' (born 27 January 1984), nicknamed \"'''Pitu'''\", is an Argentine former professional [[association footballer|footballer]] who played as a  [[midfielder]].\n\n==Club career==\n\n===Argentina===\nPitu was born in [[Santa Fe, Argentina|Santa Fe]]. He started his career in [[Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe]], base in his hometown, from which he was loaned firstly to [[CD Palestino|Palestino]] and subsequently to Iraklis. After being released by Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe he played for a brief period for [[Aris Thessaloniki F.C.|Aris]] in the Greek Superleague, before returning on a free transfer to Iraklis during the 2010 winter transfer window.\n\n===Iraklis===\nPitu joined [[Iraklis F.C.|Iraklis]] on loan during the summer of 2007. He made his league debut for his new club in a match against [[Atromitos F.C.|Atromitos]] for the fifth round of the [[2007\u201308 Superleague Greece|2007\u201308 season]], replacing [[Giannis Papadopoulos]] in the 56th minute of the match.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/matchStories/172682.html|script-title=el:\u0391\u03c4\u03c1\u03cc\u03bc\u03b7\u03c4\u03bf\u03c2-\u0397\u03c1\u03b1\u03ba\u03bb\u03ae\u03c2 1-1|date=21 October 2007|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> He continued to appear regularly for the club until the end of the season and he even managed to score his first goal for Iraklis, in a match against [[OFI Crete|OFI]].<ref name=\"OFI\">{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/matchStories/193320.html|script-title=el:\u0397\u03c1\u03b1\u03ba\u03bb\u03ae\u03c2-\u039f\u03a6\u0397 1-0|date=30 March 2008|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> It was a crucial, match deciding, goal, scored in the injury time of the match, disengaging Iraklis from the relegation battle.<ref name=\"OFI\"/> In the end of the season he counted 1 goal out of 20 league appearances.\n\n===Aris===\nOn 31 August 2009, Pitu signed for [[Aris F.C. (Thessaloniki)|Aris]] on a free transfer.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=insports.gr|url=http://www.insports.gr/index.php?s=1&c=1&p=479&cat=7&arthro=19076&nav=%C1%D1%C7%D3:%20-%D0%DF%F4%EF%F5-%20%C3%EA%E1%F1%F3%DF%E1%20%EF%2013%EF%F2|script-title=el:\u0391\u03a1\u0397\u03a3: -\u03a0\u03af\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5- \u0393\u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1 \u03bf 13\u03bf\u03c2|date=31 August 2009|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> He made his debut for Aris in a 1\u20131 away draw against [[Panthrakikos]], as he replaced his teammate [[Darcy Dolce Neto|Neto]] in the 76th minute.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/Soccer/Hellas/Superleague/Panthrakikos_Aris/251612.html|script-title=el:\u03a0\u03b1\u03bd\u03b8\u03c1\u03b1\u03ba\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc\u03c2-\u0386\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 1-1|date=3 October 2009|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> Pitu scored his only goal for Aris in a cup match against [[Aspropyrgos Enosis|Aspropyrgos]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/Soccer/Hellas/GreekCup/Aspropyrgos_Aris/253802.html|script-title=el:\u0391\u03c3\u03c0\u03c1\u03cc\u03c0\u03c5\u03c1\u03b3\u03bf\u03c2-\u0386\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 3-4|date=28 October 2010|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> He contributed in Aris' campaign as, in a match against [[AEL 1964 FC|AEL]], he hit the corner by which his teammate [[Sebastian Abreu]] scored the equaliser for his team.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/Soccer/Hellas/Superleague/Larisa_Aris/254026.html|script-title=el:\u0391\u0395\u039b - \u0386\u03c1\u03b7\u03c2 2-2|date=31 October 2009|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> He managed to appear in total of 10 matches for Aris before being released by the club on 1 February 2010.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/Soccer/Hellas/Superleague/Aris/262350.html|script-title=el:\u03a4\u03ad\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2 \u03bf \u03a0\u03af\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0393\u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1 \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc \u03c4\u03bf\u03bd \u0386\u03c1\u03b7|date=1 February 2010|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref>\n\n===Iraklis===\nOn the very same day of his release Pitu signed a contract with former club [[Iraklis F.C.|Iraklis]].<ref>{{cite web|publisher=in.gr|url=http://sports.in.gr/football/superleague/article/?aid=1101381|script-title=el:\u039f \u0397\u03c1\u03b1\u03ba\u03bb\u03ae\u03c2 \u03c3\u03c5\u03bc\u03c6\u03ce\u03bd\u03b7\u03c3\u03b5 \u03bc\u03b5 \u03a0\u03af\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5 \u0393\u03ba\u03b1\u03c1\u03c3\u03af\u03b1 \u03ba\u03b1\u03b9 \u03a1\u03b9\u03bc\u03cc\u03bb\u03bd\u03c4\u03b9|date=1 February 2010|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> The debut in this second spell for Iraklis was made in a local derby match against [[PAOK F.C.|PAOK]] that ended 1\u20131.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Contra.gr|url=http://www.contra.gr/Soccer/Hellas/Superleague/Iraklis_PAOK/262926.html|script-title=el:\u0397\u03c1\u03b1\u03ba\u03bb\u03ae\u03c2 - \u03a0\u0391\u039f\u039a 1-1|date=7 February 2010|language=Greek|accessdate=31 January 2011}}</ref> Until the end of the season he featured in a total of ten games for Iraklis.\n\n===Atromitos===\nFollowing the Iraklis's relegation, he joined [[Superleague Greece|Greek First Division]] side [[Atromitos F.C.|Atromitos]] on 29 June 2011, signing a two-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atromitosfc.gr/english/news/details/?id=645|title=Pitu Garcia inks Atromitos FC contract|publisher=[[Atromitos FC]]|date=29 June 2011|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110929001941/http://www.atromitosfc.gr/english/news/details/?id=645|archivedate=29 September 2011}}</ref>\n\n===PAS Giannina===\nOn 5 August 2019, Pitu signed for [[PAS Giannina F.C.|PAS Giannina]] on a free transfer.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pasgiannina.gr/transfer/welcome-miguel-sebastian-pitu-garcia/|title=WELCOME MIGUEL SEBASTI\u00c1N \u00abPITU\u00bb GARC\u00cdA|date=5 August 2019}}</ref> He appeared in total of 9 matches, 7 in the championship and 2 in the [[Greek Cup]]. After the end of a match against [[Levadiakos F.C.|Levadiakos]], he announced his decision to retire from football.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://super-fm.gr/54908/pitoy-pira-tin-apofasi-na-stamatiso-to-podosfairo-quot/|title=\u03a0\u03af\u03c4\u03bf\u03c5: \u00ab\u03a0\u03ae\u03c1\u03b1 \u03c4\u03b7\u03bd \u03b1\u03c0\u03cc\u03c6\u03b1\u03c3\u03b7 \u03bd\u03b1 \u03c3\u03c4\u03b1\u03bc\u03b1\u03c4\u03ae\u03c3\u03c9 \u03c4\u03bf \u03c0\u03bf\u03b4\u03cc\u03c3\u03c6\u03b1\u03b9\u03c1\u03bf\u00bb|last=|first=|date=20 January 2020|website=|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{BDFA|31298}}\n* {{K League player|20160242}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Garcia, Miguel Sebastian}}\n[[Category:1984 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Santa Fe, Argentina]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Argentine footballers]]\n[[Category:Argentine expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Aris Thessaloniki F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Iraklis Thessaloniki F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Club Deportivo Palestino footballers]]\n[[Category:Uni\u00f3n de Santa Fe footballers]]\n[[Category:Atromitos F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Volos N.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:PAS Giannina F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Seongnam FC players]]\n[[Category:Super League Greece players]]\n[[Category:K League 1 players]]\n[[Catego